            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_160gc' title='Col. 160GC &mdash; HL Deb 29 April 2004 vol 660 c160GC' name='column_160gc' href='#column_160gc' rel='bookmark'>160GC</a>
            when the conditions I described earlier are triggered. That is the first point. The second point is that this will be prescribed in regulations and it will be fair. It will not happen that a local authority will say to a utility, "Resurface this road because it is unsightly and you were working on it 10 years ago". I hope that when the draft regulations are available the noble Viscount will be reassured on that point.
          </p>
